caption: Came here on the recommendation of the B&B we were staying at. Located in a historic building, did not disappoint. Be fore dinner had a few cocktails and the bartender knew what he was doing. My bride had a Manhattan and I had a Rob Roy. Both drinks were perfect. My better half had the butternut squash soup and Beef Wellington. Loved it. I had the duck breast. Yummy. Had the bread pudding for dessert. Was okay. Not my favorite. Overall a nice dining experience.

Food was more than decent. Service was kind of a pain.  Our server couldn't and didn't keep any of our orders straight. Every time anyone ordered anything, the server disconsolately polled us to see who actually wanted what they'd brought. After the fourth time this happened, I was pretty over it.  The food was great. I enjoyed the meal I ordered, and I'd go back after we've all had a chance to recover from the changes brought in by the pandemic.  Decent beer selection, but I wish they had some brews in tap.

New favorite spot! Read the reviews before going and everything lived up to the hype. We had the scrumptious crab cake as a small plate before dinner (I could have eaten 10 of those). The beef wellington was cooked to perfection and absolutely devine! And to say the service was great is an understatement! The drinks were fast, never left with anything less than half a glass of water, and the waiter led me to a perfect cocktail choice. Can't wait to go back and try the rack of lamb!

We're so glad we bypassed pub grub to enjoy sidewalk dining at this excellent restaurant. The food was great - with amazingly fresh herbs from the rooftop garden. The friendly chef took us on a mini-tour of the garden and our waitstaff was so kind in keeping our food covered and warm for us for when we returned. An all-around excellent experience. Will definitely eat here again when in Springfield - and I look forward to learning more about the restaurant's history.

We went here for dinner while we were in Springfield visiting Abe sites. We walked from our hotel. Good food and good service. Had sea bass and Salmon. Good cocktails too. Not a lot of restaurants open so I guess only the strong survive. I highly recommended this place.

We really enjoy Morina's. The food is great and staff are friendly. During the lockdown, we utilized their delivery service and had no problems with them. Thanks so much for you service to the community!
Great Food and Service!
Love this place so much.

We're so glad we bypassed pub grub to enjoy sidewalk dining at this excellent restaurant. The food was great - with amazingly fresh herbs from the rooftop garden. The friendly chef took us on a mini-tour of the garden and our waitstaff was so kind in keeping our food covered and warm for us for when we returned.
Beef Wellington with a Kir Royale. Fantastic Service. Comfy Environment. Just Wonderful.
Great restaurant in downtown Springfield.  We had the beef wellington and Caesar salad. Both were very good.
Food ordered tonight cold an unseasoned. Tried microwave and through it away. It was picked up on time with a 10 minute drive.

We went here for dinner while we were in Springfield visiting Abe sites. We walked from our hotel. Good food and good service. Had sea bass and Salmon. Good cocktails too. Not a lot of restaurants open so I guess only the strong survive. Love the  apple crisp on winter with ice cream. Everything is quality yet relaxing.

Just went for lunch again. A few tourists were there. It's one of the few places you can eat downtown that has a great atmosphere of wood paneling and banquette seating. They have a better choice for vegetarians than most places. The food is generally good but sometimes falls short depending on what you have.  Full service.

I write to verify that what they had before Covid remains well in place.  We ate inside and it is the same warm and friendly place.  They clearly respect Covid protocols.   The staff were all warm and friendly.  I find this to be a dining respite in a somewhat abrasive world.  And the minestrone is still the best anywhere.

Just went for lunch again. A few tourists were there. It's one of the few places you can eat downtown that has a great atmosphere of wood paneling and banquette seating. They have a better choice for vegetarians than most places. The food is generally good but sometimes falls short depending on what you have.
Very elegant dining beautiful decor and romantic candlelit tables. Great food and service!
Delicious meals, very friendly staff!

Maldaner's is probably Springfield's oldest restaurant, and I don't think the menu has changed much. (I believe that Mrs. Lincoln's favorite dish is still on the menu.) It's good, but in my opinion, not good enough to justify the prices. Because of the ambiance and reputation, for special occasions I think this is still Springfield''s "go to", so if you're going for the occasion, this is your place.
Great food! It was my first time there. I'll go back again when I'm in Springfield! 😁

The staff were all warm and friendly.  I find this to be a dining respite in a somewhat abrasive world.  And the minestrone is still the best anywhere. great
My wife and I come here every anniversary. Do yourself a favor and have the rack of lamb. I've never had better. It's rich, and tender, and perfectly seasoned and seared. A true masterpiece.

Maldaner's is fine dining.  This evening, we enjoyed Minestrone, Beef Wellington, the Fish with Pancetta and Tomato Pesto (with spaghetti squash), and, of course, Brandy Alexander.  I LOVED the fish.  The pastry on the Beef Wellington was burnt on the bottom, but everything else was delicious!

This wonderful "old" American restaurant may not need more good reviews, but we will add one anyway.  In this somewhat turbulent moment, it was so nice to step back and dine in a comfortable environment.  They are clearly conscious about "Covid safety", which is now our first priority.  The staff were all upbeat and professional, and their minestrone is still the best I have experienced.
The prime rib was excellent.  As was the lemon sorbet dessert.

One of the best Route 66 restaurants. We have traveled extensively along Route 66 from Chicago to Arizona and this is by far one of the best.   It is pricier than many of the other restaurants but it is vastly superior in so many ways including service and quality of food.  The traditional "horseshoe" is outstanding and the cheese sauce is freshly made.  Don't skip this place if you are driving Route 66 and passing through Springfield,  IL.
Great service. Wonderful lunch menu.
Amazing food!!

I ordered lunch and it was the best I ever had. I'd give them 10 stars if I could. The food was prepared perfect hot when I received it. I will he ordering again. Thank you for a fantastic luvh.

Very disappointed in the dinner here last night. I had ordered the Beef Wellington and when I received it, the beef was way overcooked, tasted old and hamburger like. The vegetables were not season at all and the mashed potatoes were over salted.

Enjoyed a really nice breakfast buffet this morning,  feet scrambled eggs, sausage links, bacon, cheese blintz, coffee, orange juice, pastries.  This is a beautiful historic location serving freshly prepared  upscale gourmet foods. Totally enjoyed this experience. Yes I recommend Maldaners.

Nice quaint setting with an upscale feel. Enjoyed the Duck Confit which was cooked very nicely, juicy, tender, perfectly rendered fat. The chicken two ways was also delicious and full of flavor. The outdoor seating was very nice, especially tonight for the 100th Anniversary Route 66 car show. Worth the stop. No reservations required.

Service was prompt and friendly, food was delicious. We ordered the heirloom tomato appetizer, which was fresh and delicious. We also got Pork Osso Bucco and the crab cake, both of which were amazing. The crab cake came as a single large cake with massive crab chunks, perfectly cooked. Everything we got was delectable as usual, been coming here for quite a while and have never been disappointed.

We may have arrived on an "off" night, however the service was less than desirable. To it's saving grace, the cocktails were an 8 out of 10 on a very rigorous scale. The portions were small, but delectable. That said, they were not in a rush to take our order or bring the food out. Take note in case you're glancing at the menu ahead of time: there *are* items ONLY offered at lunch, but not dinner. Desserts were well worth it.

This restaurant was ok. When you initially enter it has a very high class feel. Then I was led to my table and discovered my seat was covered in duct tape.  The Beef Wellington was very lack luster. The pastry was very soggy and the steak had little to no flavor. Come here for the simple lunch menu but avoid it if you want a Michelin Star dinner. An interesting place.  It looks like either an old style steak place or maybe higher end Italian but it's got a very eclectic menu.  Lunch had salads, burgers and sandwiches besides larger meals.  I has a Monte Cristo sandwich which I've not had in years.  It was nicely done.  Not overly battered.  My only issue is no draft beer.  Pretty minor cause they do have a decent list of major and craft brands.  A good place for lunch for sure and I would guess dinner would be good as well.
I was with two friends, and we all had the fried chicken lunch special. It was very good and a winner with all of us. The green beans, which I believe were grilled, were especially good.
I was there Friday night I highly recommend ! Great food great service . Thanks guys
quality meals, mmm, yummy. Very appetizing. Prices are reasonable I would say.

I came for the beef wellington.  I left very satisfied.  Can't wait to come back and try a ribeye.  Great service amazing food. They accommodated our party of 10 with no problems.  Thanks chef and staff!

Had the BEST meal of my life!!! Excellent Staff!! Morel pie /crisp was to die for as an appetizer. My husband and I had our anniversary dinner there on the road to Chicago for our sons graduation from boot camp in the Navy..My husband bought the menu and paper and wrote my anniversary card!! They were so accommodating.. the filet was to die for too!! Wish I could post pics!!Highly recommend!! Thank you Maldaner’s we will make a drive from Texas to go back and eat again!!!

This restaurant has been around a very long time and it's great to see the some of the original wood work inside the restaurant.  The menus offer some old timey favorites as well as daily seasonal specials.  Our wait staff today was great!  We had a late lunch in the front window and did not feel rushed as we were some of the last to leave for lunch hour.

Have been before and was great. This time was a disaster. Food took forever. My pork belly starter was just some pork chops Blackened and past off for something it was not. Granted, the place was packed.. But took nearly 1 hour between order before i got the starter. And another 45 minutes before dinner. Looked like front of The house was bringing in too many drop ins, the kitchen was slammed, and the food quality suffered.

Staff was very helpful in accommodating us for our visit. Our server, Jess was excellent! The food was beyond our expectation, mussles appetizer & salad was perfect. We enjoyed the pork chop with Illinois apple sauce & the small filet with a lovely butternut squash puree! The flavors were complex & delicious. Coffee ice cream puffs were a perfect finish to a wonderful dinner. One of the best & most memorable anywhere! We will be back!

good place but variety of food is limited

We visited Springfield for the Lincoln history and needed a place for lunch. When looking at my google map I saw this well rated place and thought the history of it sounded interesting. After dining here, I wouldn’t recommend it and was surprised it had such good ratings. Our experience just didn’t have the feel of a one time deal. First and foremost the service was terrible and very slow. Keep in mind we were there clearly after the noon rush (if it exists for this place) and there were maybe 6 tables besides our own. When asked about why our order of 3 basic meals (one being a special) was not on our table after 45+ minutes, the server was rude and unapologetic. To bring it in to perspective, 2 tables that came in after us were served (including dessert) and gone before we got our food. Once we received the food, it didn’t get better. The server got one order completely wrong and the food was mediocre tasting. The drink refills weren’t even done correctly. I wasn’t impressed with the interior of the restaurant either, as it seemed dark and run down. The whole situation seems to need help, especially if you’re going to classify yourself as a fine-dining, classic kind of place. So, if you’re visiting Springfield I would highly suggest getting food elsewhere!
Always a great spot... one of our favorite places in Springfield.

I love this place when i want a taste of both worlds, being from Seattle I have had my fair share of incredible restaurants and I really appreciate the fact that Maldaner's is Green Certified and has organic fresh local food as well as their own roof top gardens. They still offer the old mid-west stogy antique feel but new thinking about Delicious food.
Wellington was under cooked and mushy

Hostess does not provide menus when seating. They come when the server finally decides to come to your table.  Sitting outside is one of their perks. Do so at your own risk as the service quality goes down when you are out of sight.  Bread and grated cheese was brought to the table after we sat. Olive oil was not. Just a little difficult to have the cheese with the bread when no oil is provided.  Don't order a medium rare prime rib at 7:30 on a saturday night. Yes, I know it was a risk. But I would also hope that an update would be provided telling me that med rare was no longer an option. It definitely came out at medium or just a touch higher.  It should not take 24 minutes to get a piece of Queen of Sheba for dessert. It was taken off the check but good grief!  Generally a fine place to have a wonderful meal. The ball was dropped during this visit. They will only get one more chance from me.
Food was excellent, service was good.
Always great food and great service
Excellent for a small city like Springfield. Great, timely service. Decent wine by the glass list. Food was really great for the price.
Food is good, but the service is too slow

Both food and atmosphere were outstanding. Romantic atmosphere. My filet was perfect. I loved the house salad. Even the coffee was good. The waiter was very knowledgeable about gluten-free options. I was impressed and can't wait to go back again next time I visit Springfield.
Visited once and found it nostalgic atmosphere.  Food was plentiful and good quality.  We will visit again. Great buffet .

Very nice restaurant, I had called ahead with a special request and they took care of it for me! Keep up the good customer service!

My mom and I found this restaurant years ago and enjoyed it very much for lunch. I brought my husband here for dinner while visiting Springfield. The place needs some sprucing up; not with the decor but the place smelled musty. By the time we left, my nose and head were stuffed up. The food was good, my steak was over cooked but my husbands’ steak was cooked perfectly. The waitstaff and receptionist were very friendly and polite. My husband called after he made the reservation and had them place a single rose at the table, which they did gladly and I was surprised by it. Next time we are down there, we are going to have lunch, (which I prefer that menu instead of the dinner menu), since my husband is not a seafood person. They have a lot of seafood appetizers and dishes on the dinner menu.

The most venerable landmark restaurant in Springfield IL. Great food, ambiance, and service. Whenever I come back to my hometown, a meal here is a must-have.

One of the finest restaurant in the Midwest. If your in Springfield area you have to take the opportunity to visit Chef Higgins at Maldaner's. We have been going there for 35 years and it will never disappoint. Great food and great service. If you are a Morel mushroom fan, you have to try Chef's Morel pie. Offered in the spring time only.

Our favorite for a moderately upscale night out in Springfiels. Extremely reliable execution on a delicious menu with the best service in town.

Maldaner's is on the higher end of the price spectrum in Springfield but always justifies it with great food and drinks. In the times I have eaten there, the food is cooked to perfection and tastes great. The Duck Confit is a personal favorite. There is also a healthy cocktail menu that I have yet to be disappointed by.

Extremely reasonable prices, excellent Monte   Cristo sandwich, great service.

Went for dinner here one night with colleagues. Atmosphere seemed to be a little on the romantic side with the white table clothes and wine glasses on the tables, but they seated us anyway. Or food was well prepared and tasted great! They have a limited selection and a bit on the higher side $20 a plate, but worth the cost. I would eat here again if in the area.

Their site says this is “One of the oldest restaurants on Historic Rt. 66 in Illinois”  It is an establishment with a classy look and feel. The prices are acceptable and they have separate lunch and dinner menus, which offer dishes from soups and salads to burgers, fish, pasta, and various meat options.  I was able to have their French Onion soup and their Monte Cristo sandwich. The french onion soup was top notch - what you would expect from this unique soup. The Monte Cristo - fan-freaking-tastic. It was actually the first Monte Cristo I had ever had and I will be disappointed in any future Monte Cristos from other establishments if they are not of this caliber.  Apparently, Maldaner’s contains a rooftop garden with beehives…
Great food and love the atmosphere.  Cheri was our watress and she really entertained our two boys!
Attended an evening meeting.  Very good service.  Prime rib was great!

Maldaners is always a good choice for special occasions. Be adventurous and try some of the menu items outside your comfort zone. There are many great items to try. It is definitely one of the pricier options in Springfield but worth it fit the quality of the menu.
